File: Moody's pointed to both weak household spending and investment and the detrimental impact of widespread power outages during the period. JOHANNESBURG - Ratings agency Moody's says there's a high possibility of a technical recession hitting the country. That's two consecutive quarters of negative growth. This week, Statistics South Africa data showed the country's economy contracted by 3.2 percent in the first three months of the year. READ: Moody's bleak on SA outlook Moody's pointed to both weak household spending and investment and the detrimental impact of widespread power outages during the period. It is the only one of three ratings agencies which still has the country on an investment grade.